📦 What is an Array?
An array is a collection of elements stored in a single variable, where all elements are of same type.
🔸 Imagine ek train ke bogies – har bogie mein number (data) hai, aur sab ek line mein lage hain.

🧠 Why use Array?
✅ To store multiple values ​​(in one variable)
✅ Fast access by index (like 0th, 1st, 2nd...)
✅ Useful in loops, searching, sorting etc.
________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

IT'S IMPORTANT :....................................... 
  Syntax in java
  // Declare an array
int[] marks = new int[5]; // 5 elements

// OR directly initialize
int[] marks = {90, 85, 77, 60, 95};

// Access elements
System.out.println(marks[0]);  // Output: 90
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________


🛑 Note: Index 0 se start hota hai.

Basics of Arrays in Java :

🧠 Why use Arrays?
Store many values without creating multiple variables
Access elements easily using index
Great for loops, calculations, and data processing
__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

  
  ✅ Array Declaration in Java
int[] numbers;         // Step 1: Declare
numbers = new int[5];  // Step 2: Allocate memory

🧠 This creates an array that can store 5 integers.

✅ Initialization (Assigning values)
numbers[0] = 10;
numbers[1] = 20;
numbers[2] = 30;
numbers[3] = 40;
numbers[4] = 50;

OR
int[] numbers = {10, 20, 30, 40, 50};  // Declare + initialize

🔎 Accessing Array Elements
System.out.println(numbers[0]);  // Output: 10
System.out.println(numbers[4]);  // Output: 50
🛑 Remember: Indexing starts from 0

🔁 Loop Through Array
for (int i = 0; i < numbers.length; i++) {
    System.out.println(numbers[i]);
}

OR
  for (int num : numbers) {
    System.out.println(num);   // Enhanced for loop
}


